cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it deals with malware detection, which is a security-related problem. It also uses deep convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for classification, which is a common technique in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE) sub-categories. However, since the focus of the paper is on the application of CNNs to malware detection, cs.CR is the most likely sub-category.
